text: Belinda Bromilow (born 21 May 1975) is an Australian actress. She is known for her roles in the Nine Network series, Doctor Doctor (2016–21) and the Hulu/Disney+ series The Great (2020–23), playing Elizabeth of Russia. Bromilow was diagnosed with bowel cancer in 2013.
